						<h2>Promotion to next semester and supplementary examination</h2>
						<p>A student is declared to have passed the semester examination when he passes in all the courses of the semester having a minimum GPA 2.00 in each course. The students declared to have passed the semester exam may register for all the courses of the next semester. <br />
						A student having a backlog of more than 4 courses in which he/she failed will not be allowed to register for the next semester. Referred Examination on the referred course or courses will normally be held with the final examination of the upcoming semester. The Referred Examinations will cover the entire syllabus of the course. Those failing in any subject of the referred examination shall have to appear again in the-semester final examination and pass the referred subjects. Otherwise the students will not be eligible to register for the higher semester. Students of the final year of a program, will be allowed to appear in not more than 4 courses or twelve credit hours in a supplementary exanimation held alter one month from publication of results of last semester final examination.
						</p>
						<h2>Attendance</h2>
						<p>All students are expected to attend classes regularly. Svlhet international University believes that regular attendance is necessary for effective learning. A student is required to attend at least 70% of all-classes held in every course in order to sit for the final examination.</p>
						<h2>Absence during Semester</h2>
						<p>A student will not be absent from quizzes, tests, mid semester exam etc., during the semester. Such absence will naturally lead to reduction in points/marks, which will count towards the final grade. Absence in semester final examination will result in F grade.</p>
						<h2>Award of Degree</h2>
						<p>The academic council will decide the minimum credit hour requirement for the award of degree in different schools of study. Total credit hours ranging from 120 and 165, depending on the discipline, should be earned to be eligible for graduation.' For a-2-year master’s program the required credit hours may be around 70.</p>
						<h2>Conduct and Discipline</h2>
						<p>A student should conform to high standard of discipline and will conduct himself  /  herself within and outside the premises of the university in a manner befitting the student of a university of national importance. He or she will show -due courtesy and consideration to the teachers and other employees of the university and good neighborliness to his or her fellow students. The students must.-also pay due attention and courtesy to visitors.</p>
						<h2>Improvement Examination</h2>
						<p>Students scoring less than 2.50 in any course may be allowed an opportunity for improvement either by doing the course afresh or by appearing only in the final examination on payment of lees deemed suitable by 'the university.</p>
						<h2>Admissions</h2>
						<p>The admission office advises the prospective regarding students and guardians admission to SIU. Students and guardians are always encouraged to visit the campus for individual counseling. </p>
						<h2>Undergraduate Admissions Criteria</h2>
						<p>Admission requirements for undergraduate program are as follows: <br />
						At least 2.5 grade point in each of the Secondary School Certificate (SSC) and Higher Secondary Certificate (HSC) from a board or university or equivalent examinations
						</p>
						<h2>International Students</h2>
						<p>For the purpose of admission, interactional applicants are defined as all persons who are not citizens of Bangladesh. International applicants, who seek admission at SIU, must meet the same academic standards for admission as those required of local students. Since there are wider variations in educational systems throughout the world, international applicants are selected on the basis of their academic work, proficiency in English and Mathematics, probability of success in the chosen curricula, and certification of adequate financial resources.</p>
						<h2>Transfer of Credits</h2>
						<p>Credits earned at previously attended colleges and universities will be evaluated for acceptance toward SIU degrees by faculty members. Transcripts from previously attended institutions must be submitted for evaluation. A student who wishes to seek transfer with his earned credit to other universities at home and abroad may be allowed to do so. Credits earned at SIU are accepted by all universities at home and abroad. Some of our students have already migrated to foreign universities and their credits earned here have been accepted.</p>
						<h2>Graduate Admission Criteria</h2>
						<p>Although initially SIU is only offering undergraduate level courses in certain disciplines, the university intends to start graduate level program as soon as adequate facilities are available for incoming graduate students.Interested students of graduate program at the SIU are requested to contact the respective departments, and/or the dean of schools/admissions office for further information. At present the university has MBA program and minimum qualification for admission is graduation and a total of 5 points.</p>
						<h2>General Application Procedures and Application Forms</h2>
						<p>Students interested in enrolling at SIU should collect in person or send a bank draft/pay order for Tk. 300.00 or US $ 10.00 or equivalent in the name of the Sylhet International University to the Dean of Schools/Admission officer for an application form and instructions concerning the admission process. The completed application form should be returned to the dean's/admissions office. All correspondence and inquiries concerning admission to the university should be addressed to the dean/admission officer.</p>
